    "summary": "Simo Hafidi has accumulated a solid experience and knowledge in economics, especially in Finance and Controlling disciplines. Twenty years ago, he started his first position in the Japanese computers and IT solutions manufacturer NEC in the Netherlands to grow to managerial positions in global organizations such as Avery Dennison, Atradius, Randstad, and Volvo. Each step was an addition that deepened his skills in the latest financial and controlling challenges of global farms. Lastly, he engaged in supporting startups by providing counseling in Finance and Controlling strategies. \n\nBesides this state-of-the-art experience, Simo Hafidi has chosen a diverse academic path. After his Bachelor's degree in Computer Programming, he pursued a Bachelor's degree in International Business Management in Amsterdam. Next to this degree, he obtained certificates in management accounting. Later, he invested in a Master in Public Administration major in Security and Crises management at the university of Leiden. Aiming to bring his expertise and knowledge in finance and controlling to the highest levels, he enrolled in the prestigious and challenging Post-master of Finance and Controlling at the Erasmus University of Rotterdam.\n\nHis verifiable records of achievements can only witness a solid value with accomplished leadership in multi-national organizations.",
